      "correct_answer": 1,
      "explanation": "Sarah must decline the offer and maintain her independence. Accepting any financial inducement from a subject of an investigation creates a conflict of interest and compromises the fraud examiner's integrity and independence. Ethical standards require fraud examiners to resist any pressure to limit or bias their findings, regardless of financial incentives. The fraud examiner has a duty to report all material findings discovered during the investigation.",
      "topic": "Independence and Conflicts of Interest",
      "num": 14
