    {
      "question": "During a fraud examination, you discover that the subject of your investigation is a close personal friend of your supervisor who hired you for this engagement. Your findings indicate significant evidence of fraudulent activity. What is the MOST appropriate course of action according to ethical standards for fraud examiners?",
      "options": {
        "A": "Complete the investigation but soften the language in your report to minimize potential conflict between your supervisor and their friend",
        "B": "Disclose the relationship to appropriate parties and discuss whether your continued involvement presents a conflict of interest or independence issue",
